d=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ene1665702759768.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ene1665702759768.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ene1665702759768.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ene1665702759768\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Operation activated by the SAX parser when a processing instruction is encountered.\n </p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ene1665702759768_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ene1665702759768__codeblock_mk1_324_hwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation PROCESSINGINST\n  params\n     string Target: in\n     string Data: in \n  endparams\n\nImplement your code here\n\nend; PROCESSINGINST operation</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665702759768__section_g4m_324_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1126891e53\">Parameters</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ene1665702759768__ul_otf_k24_hwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ene1665702759768__li_d48419e1_d48420e1_d48421e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ene1665702759768__li_d48422e1_d48423e1_d48424e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Data</var>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665702759768__section_dlz_m24_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1126891e75\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ene1665702759768__p_d137165e1_d137166e1_d137167e1\">Processing instructions specify application-specific\n        data, similar to <code class=\"ph codeph\">#pragma</code> for C compilers.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ene1665702759768__p_d137168e1_d137169e1_d137170e1\">A processing instruction has the format\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;?target data?/&gt;</code>. The target is returned in the parameter\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>, the rest up to the closing <code class=\"ph codeph\">?/&gt;</code> is returned\n        in parameter <var class=\"keyword varname\">Data</var>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527217\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527217\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "PROCESSINGINST Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Operation activated by the SAX parser when a processing instruction is encountered. Explain this code operation PROCESSINGINST params string Target: in string Data: in endparams Implement your code here end; PROCESSINGINST operation Copy Parameters Target Data Description Processing instructions specify application-specific data, similar to #pragma for C compilers. A processing instruction has the format <?target data?/> . The target is returned in the parameter Target , the rest up to the closing ?/> is returned in parameter Data . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}